propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propComponent:
The component used for the root node.
Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.
propSelected: If `true` the pagination item is selected.
propShape: The shape of the pagination item.
propSize: The size of the pagination item.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesPage: Styles applied to the root element if `type="page"`.
stylesSizeSmall: Styles applied applied to the root element if `size="small"`.
stylesSizeLarge: Styles applied applied to the root element if `size="large"`.
stylesText: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="text"`.
stylesTextPrimary: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="text"` and `color="primary"`.
stylesTextSecondary: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="text"` and `color="secondary"`.
stylesOutlined: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="outlined"`.
stylesOutlinedPrimary: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="outlined"` and `color="primary"`.
stylesOutlinedSecondary: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="outlined"` and `color="secondary"`.
stylesRounded: Styles applied to the root element if `rounded="true"`.
stylesEllipsis: Styles applied to the root element if `type="start-ellipsis"` or `type="end-ellipsis"`.
stylesFocusVisible: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if keyboard focused.
stylesDisabled: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if `disabled={true}`.
stylesSelected: Pseudo-class applied to the root element if `selected={true}`.
stylesIcon: Styles applied to the icon element.
